frameDefinitions: This frame contains words that describe an Item's static position on a scale with respect to some property Variable.  '' 'Dried fruits are especially high in fibre, as are pulses.'
A Subset is profiled against the Group it belongs to.

This frame consists of words that indicate that an Agent or a Cause affects the position of an Item on some scale (the Attribute) to change it from an initial value (Value_1) to an end value (Value_2).
A Part is considered to be a member of the set described by the Total.
A member or members of a Class have just been  mentioned or are present in the discourse setting and now a different instance  (or group of instances) of the same class is referred to.
frameExamples: Dried fruits are especially <t>high</t> in fibre, as are pulses.
<t>Of</t> all scenes that evoke rural England, this is one of the loveliest.
The company is <t>raising</t> the final dividend from 4.34p to 4.57p, to boost the total by 5.3 percent to 6.36p.
Dr. Nelson <t>numbers</t> among the world?s foremost geotechnical engineering experts.
My husband left me for <t>another</t> woman -- and now wants to get back together again!
listRoleDefinitions: <fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity whose scalar property is specified.

<fen>Variable</fen> is the scalar property that the <fen>Item</fen> possesses.

<fex name='Item'>Soda</fex> is <t>high</t> <fex name='Variable'>in sugar</fex>.
The <fen>Value</fen> is the position or range of positions on the scale that the Item occupies.  This is normally implicit in the LU.
The <fen>Group</fen> of entities which includes the <fen>Subset</fen>.
The person who causes an entity (Item) to change its positon on a scale with respect to some property (Variable).
The scale along which the <fen>Item</fen> ranges in value.
The entity whose position along a scale is being changed.
The force that causes the change.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the value of an <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The complex multi-part entity of which a constituent <fen>Part</fen> is specified.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the subset relation holds.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the subset relation holds.
The general category of entity which has been referred to.
The instance of the <fen>Class</fen> that is added to the <fen>Initial_set</fen> of entities in the <fen>Class</fen>.
The previously mentioned group of entities of the <fen>Class</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The rain</fex> increased the river's flow rate to an astonishing million gallons per second.
As a result, they raised prices <fex>in Peoria</fex>.
As a representative in Congress in the years 1783-85, Gerry numbered <fex>among those who had possessed talent as Revolutionary agitators and wartime leaders</fex>.
Just be glad that <fex>you</fex> number among the living.
<fex>At that time</fex>, the factory numbered among the largest in the western half of North America.
<fex>In Europe</fex>, the sport counts among the economic branches of industry which generate employment among the young people.
My Husband left me for another <fex>man</fex>!
A further five incursions <fex>over and above those noted for 1995</fex> took place in the first three months of 1996.
